In this article, President Trump responds to remarks made by House Speaker Nancy Pelosi about him being engaged in a cover-up. He asserts that he is the most transparent president in history and criticizes the investigations into his administration, stating that there was no collusion or obstruction. Trump also mentions his accomplishments in the economy and job market, and expresses frustration with the ongoing investigations hindering progress on issues like infrastructure. He concludes by expressing concern about the potential for future impeachment proceedings against a president of any party.